narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned to think differently about the concept of fear and analyze philosophical texts more closely than I ever knew how.

I became much more adept at analyzing film through this course. I felt that I came to understand the importance of describing action as well as providing analysis. I also learned how to differentiate an interpretive paper from a normal one.
I developed my interpretational writing skills and my knowledge of philosophy and certain classic political treatises

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: good distribution of philosophy, literature and film. Well paced course. Interesting content. Professors worked well with students and got to know us. Professors also worked well with each other and their understanding of each other made the class flow very smoothly. Weaknesses: only that discussion sometimes lulled. This seminar should be more selective.
I can't think of any blatant weaknesses. Maybe the weekly film time being at an inconvenient time?

Having two professors was a great aspect of the course and listening to their discourse was fantastic. the films we watched seemed like very poor and disengaging choices when we consider the literature provided.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. Great course that opened me up to a lot of texts/films I would've never read or saw before if I hadn't taken this course.
Yes the teachers were excellent an the coursework was extremely interesting!
